## Questions

Topic: RDCO Interpretation Limitation

Q.1: If the measured RDCO value of a transition is close to 1 when gated on a known quadrupole transition, can we confidently conclude that the transition is quadrupole? What experimental factors might influence this interpretation?
Concepts involved:
• RDCO ratios
• multipole mixing
• detector geometry
• statistical uncertainty

Topic: RDCO vs IPDCO Conflict

Q.2: Suppose RDCO analysis suggests a dipole transition but IPDCO measurement indicates an electric quadrupole character. What physical or experimental factors could explain this discrepancy?
Concepts involved:
• mixed transitions (M1+E2)
• gating errors
• detector asymmetry

Topic: Gamma-Gamma Coincidence Ambiguity

Q.3: Under what circumstances can gamma–gamma coincidence measurements produce an incorrect nuclear level scheme?
Concepts involved:
• contaminant peaks
• accidental coincidences
• unresolved transitions

